Vol / Page: 24
Edition:
Quote: We were doubly anxious to be liberal after hearing a very good-tempered Maori man contrast the large-handed hospitality of his people to English travellers, with the `one pannikinful' of flour, - about half a pound, - doled out to him when he visited any one in Auckland.
